---
description: when handling errors or async actions like API calls, or network requests, or server actions
alwaysApply: false
---

- All async data fetching must include Suspense and fallback loading UI.
- Log errors to console and display user-friendly error messages.
- Never silently ignore errors.
- Include loading and error states for all async data fetching.
- When building pages and components, use suspense and skeletons for loading states.
